2022 Pakistan Floods - Displacement Analysis

An analysis of PDMA and CCCM partner data

Author

Pakistan Shelter Sector - CCCM Working Group

Published

14 October 2022

Introduction

This analysis explores current displacement figures and trends of the 2022 Pakistan floods, a basic mapping of currently known displacement sites, and analysis of flood indation changes since 31st August 2022.

Limitations: This analysis is a work-in-progress, currently focusing on the hardest hit Province of Sindh. Once time and data availability permits, the analysis will expand to Balochistan, KPK and Punjab. Currently, the site mapping section shows a small proportion of the total number of sites, due to data availablity. We plan to expand this, once data from additional districts becomes available. For this phase, only formal âTent Cityâ/âRelief Campsâ are shown, although this may be expanded to include informal sites at a later stage.

Displacement trends

Provincial-level - Sindh

According to the latest Sindh PDMA Sitrep of 12-Oct-2022, 243,030 displaced people are currently in Relief Camps, while 6,314,640 are displaced outside of them.
